    {
      "id": "PopularPost164489",
      "post_content": "*\"Why wait until 4 spells are cast to copy a spell when you can just cast [Reverberate](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reverberate) instead?\"*  \n'Cause you 're doing it wrong.  \n  \nCreature-based damage (a Tim or two, preferably [Gelectrode](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gelectrode)s, which is my personal favourite, or Goblins) will fill it with quest counters. Then it will be cracked to double the damage dealt by all your creatures and burn spells.  \n  \nActually, two of those quests fully prepared are a win condition almost by themselves...  \n  \nAs for the Storm mechanic, [Grapeshot](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Grapeshot) fits perfectly. Storm spells are separate from one another, not only rewarding you with a counter per point of damage dealt, but also allowing you to crack the quest as soon as it's reached four counters, doubling the output of the rest.  \n  \nFavourite Turn 2 win:  \n1) [Desperate Ritual](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Desperate Ritual).  \n2) [Seething Song](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Seething Song).  \n3) Cast 2 [Quests](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=197407).  \n4) [Grapeshot](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Grapeshot).  \n5) Crack... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Falgorn",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost164489\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\"><i>\"Why wait until 4 spells are cast to copy a spell when you can just cast <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Reverberate\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reverberate\">Reverberate</a> instead?\"</i><br/>'Cause you 're doing it wrong.<br/><br/>Creature-based damage (a Tim or two, preferably <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Gelectrode\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gelectrode\">Gelectrode</a>s, which is my personal favourite, or Goblins) will fill it with quest counters. Then it will be cracked to double the damage dealt by all your creatures and burn spells.<br/><br/>Actually, two of those quests fully prepared are a win condition almost by themselves...<br/><br/>As for the Storm mechanic, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Grapeshot\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Grapeshot\">Grapeshot</a> fits perfectly. Storm spells are separate from one another, not only rewarding you with a counter per point of damage dealt, but also allowing you to crack the quest as soon as it's reached four counters, doubling the output of the rest.<br/><br/>Favourite Turn 2 win:<br/>1) <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Desperate Ritual\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Desperate Ritual\">Desperate Ritual</a>.<br/>2) <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Seething Song\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Seething Song\">Seething Song</a>.<br/>3) Cast 2 <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardid=\"197407\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=197407\">Quests</a>.<br/>4) <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Grapeshot\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Grapeshot\">Grapeshot</a>.<br/>5) Crack... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 164489)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '164489'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy2685\">Falgorn</span>\r\n                                (5/28/2011 4:03:12 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"cl